{"id":"spices","term":"Spices","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Aromatic substances, of which several are named in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 30\">Ex. 30</a>. They were used in the sacred anointing oil (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 25:6\">Ex. 25:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 35:8\">35:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 9:29\">1 Chr. 9:29</a>), and in embalming the dead (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 16:14\">2 Chr. 16:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 23:56\">Luke 23:56</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 24:1\">24:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 19:39\">John 19:39</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 19:40\">40</a>). Spices were stored by Hezekiah in his treasure-house (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 20:13\">2 Kings 20:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 39:2\">Isa. 39:2</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 30","Exodus 25:6","Exodus 35:8","1 Chronicles 9:29","2 Chronicles 16:14","Luke 23:56","Luke 24:1","John 19:39","John 19:40","2 Kings 20:13","Isaiah 39:2"]}